==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tore
<hw>Tore</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably from the root of
<ets>tear</ets>; cf. W. <ets>t⟦oacute⟧r</ets> a break, cut,
<ets>t⟦oacute⟧ri</ets> to break, cut.]</ety> <def>The dead grass that
remains on mowing land in winter and spring.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

